  "market_context": "Uptrend in gold spot price with impulsive moves followed by pullbacks; analyst identified swing low at ~2228.036 and swing high at ~2301–2303 range to draw Fibonacci extensions for target identification.",
  "key_observation": "Price repeatedly reacted at key Fibonacci extension levels: reversed at 0.786 (2286.126), paused at 1.0 (2301.942), and reversed sharply at 1.618 (2347.617).",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified a clear impulsive move from swing low (~2228.036) to swing high (~2301–2303) to define the base for Fibonacci extension drawing.",
    "Step 2: Drew trend-based Fibonacci extension from swing low to swing high, then extended beyond to project targets (0.786, 1.0, 1.618).",
    "Step 3: Observed price pulling back and reversing at the 0.786 level (2286.126), confirming it as a reaction zone.",
    "Step 4: Noted price reaching the 1.0 level (2301.942) and showing strong reaction—multiple candles consolidating or reversing there.",
    "Step 5: Tracked price advancing further to the 1.618 extension (2347.617), where it reversed decisively, validating it as a high-probability target zone."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Fibonacci extension levels—especially 0.786, 1.0 (measured move), and 1.618—are reliable target zones in trending markets; price often reverses or pauses at these geometrically derived levels.",
